author: @allisongalindo2230
text: (mucho texto, gracias a los que leyeron todo) No se pero cada que escucho esta canción me recuerda a mi pasado y todo lo que cambio, lo feliz que era, todo lo que perdí, todo lo que gane, no se que es mejor, mi pasado o mi presente, que pasara conmigo, agradezco haber conocido a estos hermosos chicos que me han ayudado a seguir, quiero seguir viendo esas hermosas sonrisas que me inspiran y me dicen que siga delante, a pesar de haber perdido a mi abuela, mi tío, y creo que también debería decir mi papá, sigo adelante y quiero ser feliz con la s personas que amo, gracias Stray Kids por todo nunca me cansaré de decirlo Stray kids mi grupo favorito hermosos, talentosos, son excelentes gracias Dios por haber hecho a personas muy lindas, mi deseo es conocer a estos bellos chicos y espero se cumpla, quisiera decirles lo tanto que los aprecio, lo tanto que me ayudaron en estos momentos difíciles, aunque mi familia crea que es estúpido, ridículo, torpe lo que siento por ellos es la verdad, no puedo creer que llegaría a amar tanto a unas personas las cuales no conozco, no saben que existo pero no me arrepiento, gracias stray kids por existir, en 18 días es mi cumpleaños, mi deseo de cumpleaños es que Hyunjin vuelva, me ha dolido tanto que se fuera lo necesito de vuelta, quiero volver a ver su sonrisa, que sea mi bias me ha afectado el doble su ida, necesito que vuelva, Hyunjin regresa, sería el mejor regalo de cumpleaños, Gracias a Dios y a Stray kids estoy aquí, nunca dudaré, me encanta ver todo lo que han ganado y créanme esto es solo el principio, Stray Kids llegará a muchísimo más, serán reconocidos por lo que son, y no me importa la opinión de los demás, Stray Kids es el mejor grupo de kpop, ellos hacen sus canciones, coreografías, tienen unas vocales increíbles, sus habilidades en el rap son maravillosas, no digamos de sus coreografías, tienen visuales tremendas, en fin lo que digo es la verdad Stray Kids es el mejor grupo de kpop, los amo Stray Kids gracias Dios por cuidarme todo este tiempo, y se que lo harás por mucho mas, y así quiero que cuides de ellos ya que ellos son unas de las pocas razones que hacen feliz, en mi vida siempre será Dios el primero en Segundo mi familia y Stray Kids como el tercero ❤️

las canciones de Stray Kids me identifican demasiado... y no se porque pero eso me transmite Felicidad y paz<3
Todo el dia tengo que soportar a mi familia y sus comentarios innecesarios pero al final del dia me encuentro bien porque se que SKZ es lo mejor de este mundo, puedo recargarme a llorar en ellos sin la preocupación de que me den la espalda como todos los demas, SKZ es la causa de mi felicidad entera y siempre sera asi <3
Estoy orgullosa de ellos y de todo lo que han logrado, estoy orgullosa de saber que elegi a un gran grupo al igual que un gran y hermoso fandom
Stray Kids, Stay, Les amo gracias por  salvarme de mi propia mente❤️

author: @irulansanz1725
text:
I just want to say: " Merci Stray Kids, vous êtes les meilleurs. Tous les jours j'écoute vos chansons. Elles me rendent heureuse et me donne de la force pour continué de vivre. Vous êtes si mignon, gentil, beau .... Vous avez tant de talent ! La première fois que j'ai lu les paroles de Voices j'ai pleuré (et je pleure toujours). J'espère que les concerts pourront reprendre, et j'espère que vous viendrez en France 😉. Merci pour tous ce que vous faites pour les Stay vous êtes des garçons géniaux, qui méritent tous l'amour du monde !"  
In english: "Thanks Stray Kids, you are the best. Every day I listen to your songs. They make me happy and give me strength to continue living. You are so cute, kind, beautiful .... You have so much talent! The first time I read the lyrics to Voices I cried (and I still cry). I hope that the concerts can resume, and I hope that you will come to France 😉. Thank you for all you do for the Stay you are awesome boys, who all deserve the love of the world !"

I love you all ! 💜
I make Stray Kids stay ! And you ?

author: @americanoooochoachoa4396
text:
Ahh yess the song that made me stan stray kids! I'm starting to remember the day I first stumbled upon skz performance video of god's menu while browsing yt. I don't remember much on how I became i stay actually, the only thing I remember was I started listening to some of Skz song and it got me interested. 

Back then I was struggling with low-self esteem, fear of talking, fear of mistakes, restlessness, fear of going outside and talking to people. I even often find myself lost and frustrated. Of course, talking to someone or asking for help would've  made things easier for me but I couldn't bring myself to do it due to fear. So I handled things on my own...

Looking back at my past, skz songs seriously helped me face through my hard times! Their songs are so comforting, some of their songs are also relatable, some are cheerful and fun, some gives me strength to face my problems. Skz songs are indeed one of a kind. 

Now, I'm currently improving myself, and I'm not struggling as much as before! :) 

Ty skz and stays!!! I'm so grateful to stumble upon skz!  There are a lot of things that I seriously wanna add but I can't bring myself to do it. Since I'm terrible at expressing. Plus, English isn't my native language.

Also, Ty for those who took their time on reading this! Have a nice day/night/noon/evening 😆😊

author: @adagio0590
text:
¿QUÉ TAL, STAYS? ¡NO OLVIDEN VOTAR POR CHAN EN FANPLUS, CATEGORÍA "THE BEST LEADER CONTEST"!

¿QUIEREN SABER CÓMO VOTAR? ¡SIGAN LEYENDO ESTE COMENTARIO!

Sé que se ve largo y a algunxs les dará flojera, ¡pero es sencillo! Ánimo, stay, podemos lograr que Chan gane ^^


-Primero tienen que instalarse la aplicación Fanplus.
-Ya cuando la tengan instalada la abren (ps obvio xd) y se registran, acpetan los términos, bla, bla, bla (lo bueno es que está en inglés), también deberán ponerse un nombre de usuario.
-Luego les aparecerá un coso que dice "Select stars", o sea "Seleccionar estrellas" y ahí ustedes seleccionan a Stray Kids y luego eligen a su bias.
-Ahí entraran al inicio de la app y les aparecerá algo que dice "Enter recommender and collect 500 cash" (si no les aparece, vayan a configuación y seleccionen "Enter your referrer"), entonces ustedes pueden poner mi usuario que es "LoveSKZforever", luego tendrán que verificar su cuenta, enonces pondrán sus números de celular y les enviarán por mensaje un código, el cual tendrán que introducir en 60 segundos o menos. Ya verificada les volverá a aparecer la pestaña en donde pusieron mi usuario y le darán click a "Entered, give me cash!", y esto hará que reciban tanto ustedes como yo, 500 monedas para comprar votos.
-Para comprar los votos deberán salir de configuración e ir a la pestaña que dice "Vote" en la barra de abajo y les aparecerá una parte con opciones, ustedes pondrán "Buy Votes" y luego "Go to item shop", ahí les aparecerán opciones y darám click a comprar 3.000 votos con 500 monedas.
-Una vez comprados los votos, irán a "Vote" de nuevo,  donde bajarán hasta donde diga "The Best Leader Contest" y allí darán click, entonces les aparecerán los idols líderes para votar, buscarán a Chan (que en el momento en que escribo esto está en tercer puesto) y le darán click a "vote", luego seleccionarán la cantidad de votos que quieren dejar, darán click a "vote" y volverán a confirmar. Y LISTO!

PUEDEN SEGUIR VOTANDO, y para eso necesitarán comprar más votos, los cuales conseguiran en la "Item shop" y deberán comprar con monedas. Las monedas se pueden conseguir de distintas maneras, ya sea comprándolas con dinero real, viendo anuncios (en la parte que dice "Watch Video Ads" pueden ver hasta treinta anuncios por día, y con cada anuncio que vean pueden ganar 15 votos, sin necesidad de tener que ir a la tienda a comprarlos, directamente ya les depositan votos), completando misiones, resolviendo encuestas, etc.

Y ESO ES TODO, NO SÉ SI LO EXPLIQUÉ BIEN, SI TIENEN ALGUNA DUDA PUEDEN PREGUNTARME!

author: @sweetie1272
text:
This song talks about how people just talk and there comes a point in your life where you only hear their voices, cause they silence yours *"I can't hear my voices"*

The voices of others have already stayed in your head and it is difficult to take them out to listen to yourself, voices that only suffocate
Criticism, insults, scolding, hurtful words, everything is still there and annoying. Your own voice keeps trying to sound louder, you try to speak to yourself but it's impossible.

C. Channiefreckles

My first language is not English but..

author: @Amyafterhours
text: This song deserves so much more recognition & hype. Not only this one but their first 3 albums INCLUDING their predebut one 'Mixtape'. You really dont see "kpop" idols talk about stuff this straightforward or even incorporate it into their dance this "aggressively". Stray Kids are one of the few artist that that do that back to back and it coms from them genuinely. Songs like this are why I say they don't really fit the "kpop" genre. Not bc im trying to say they're "above" kpop or anything but because they really don't just make Korean pop music. They have so much diversity in their music whether it's in genre, chord progression, song structure, everything. If you dig into the technicalities, they're are so so unique and I just dont think labeling them as "kpop" is fitting, it never was. These boys are pushing boundaries to see how far they can go & I think thats what is going to give them even greater success. I'm so proud to support them, and excited to see what their new music will contain as far as content goes!

author: @faraheladawiyah
text:
Pertama kali denger tahun 2018 dan nggak ngerti arti lirik bahasa koreanya. Tapi dengerin lirik bahasa inggris sama emosi mereka, lagu ini dale banget. Langsung jatuh cinta. Padahal saya kira lagu barat yg dicover ke bahasa korea. Ternyata mmg lagu mereka sendiri. First impresaion yg sangat2 membekas. Dalam hati. "Saya harus mendukung musik mereka" 

Jadi, mereka pengalaman saya membeli album resmi KPop walau udh dengerin musik kpop dr 2004. Sampek sekarang album mereka terpajang di lemari. Itu sebagai bentuk apresiasi atas musik2 yg bisa menyentuh saya. Usia saya bukan untuk ngestan group ini itu. Tapi saya akan ttap mendudukung anak2 ini. 

Tetap semangat , nuna akan selalu mendukung kalian, apapun yg terjadi. Jangan pernah malu memperkenalkan karya kalian ke seluruh dunia. Jangan ubah gaya kalian hanya untuk menyenangkan orang lain. Tapi kalau gaya kalian berubah memang kalian ingin mencoba sesuatu yg baru nuna dukung kalian. :)

author: @dubuque2526
text:
Hello, I'm a new stay and let me share something:
I have social anxiety issues or that 'voice' whenever I try to talk to someone, including my friends and me. I always staying away from my friends to cry alone because there always an invisible voice saying I don't deserve to have friends, they are just pretending to be, and they secretly hate you for who you are. I always just thinking about negative things and problems that didn't even exist. I don't have the confidence and encouragement to talk about my problems to them because I felt I'm just a problematic boy who has problems literally with small things.

Then, that day. I don't even want to talk with them. I just zipped my mouth whenever they are messaging to our group. I just saw how happy their conversation without me. Whenever I try to join, the voice just keeps telling me that I will ruin the fun and they will hate me for joining the conversation. I don't know why I can't do it. I can't fight that voice and always ending up losing. I just end up crying almost every night thinking why am I like this? Why I can't be a normal person? Should I end here right now?

As I stan stray kids and hear this song. This masterpiece just saved me. When I heard the chorus, This gives me strength that I will do it.  I never ever felt to be free from these voices. It's felt like freedom. There are more things I want to do before I cut the last breath. So sooner or later, I will talk to my friends about my problems.

Thank you, Stray kids. Thank you so much for saving me from these voices inside of my head. I will support you until the end.

author: @meowyoi
text: it's already 5am in here and I just wanna say how this song always make me cry. this is the song I always listen the most when my dog died. She's the longest dog I've ever had. She had a single puppy, it's so tiny baby and suddenly it died. Because she wasn't feeding it well, I was trying to feed her puppy all by myself but when I was looking for materials that U need to use,when I came back to them,her puppy already died. she was crying, after that we bury her puppy. she was finding it all-day long. then there's this day when we taught she was gone, because she's out of nowhere in our home. It was raining outside but I still need to find her,but I haven't found her. then the next day she came back,after that she became so aggressive,she always fought with our other dogs. she always causes fights, then my family said that we should leave her on a abandon place because she might also bite us people. then my cousin and grandpa leave her on that place, later on we saw her walking to our house. she was so thirsty,she would cry again finding for her baby. we feel so bad for leaving her,we have no choice and we just let her stay to us. then on the night time I was watching SKZ contents,my cousin suddenly came to me saying that she already died. and I can't-.. she's the longest dog I've ever had. she and her baby along with her brother can rest in peace now. Thank you SKZ for calming me down and making me happy and warm until now.

author: @alienhannie3322
text:
This comment is just about myself. You can keep scrolling.

This song made me join the fandom. When I heard "Voices" I cried. Maybe you can find it strange but yeah I cried so hard. I was know God's Menu and Victory Song but Voices made me a STAY while crying so hard. I am not regret. I'm proud with being a STAY. Beacuse our SKZ has songs like Glow, Grow Up, Mixtape #3, Voices... 

In daily life I'm a panicked person. I want to say somebody to me "Take it slow." and Seungmin says it in My Pace. 

I have sleeping problems and Insomnia helps me with Hyunjin's beatiful voice. 

I'm a hardworking student but I keep thinking about "Is it enough? Should I study more?" but when I think something like that Mixtape#3 helps me and says that I'm doing well. 

I am a asocial person I don't have so many friends and I don't have self-confidence too but when I listen Phobia I felt that I am not the only one. 

When I listen Slump I remember my old and peaceful memories. 

When I think that my teenager years are about to finish I listen 19 and get lost in the lyrics. 

I am that kind of person who runs so many thoughts in her head and 'm getting tired of myself when it happens I listen TMT. 

And so many things like that. Stray Kids' songs are just about me being myself. They making me feel that I am not the only one and I can keep going. I am so thankful them. Cuz you know even you have so many supportful people around you it sometimes become harder and you can't tell anybody... I don't know. It is different for me. Stray Kids is special for me. 

I am so glad to meeting them. They filled the emptiness in my life.

(Sorry English is not my first language. I just wanted wrote it in English because maybe one of them can read it :") )

author: @whoisconihey3625
text:
La lasaña de carne a la boloñesa no es sólo el plato favorito de Garfield, es uno de los platos más famosos e internacionales de la cocina italiana. La lasaña tal y como la conocemos hoy, no se popularizó hasta bien entrado el siglo XVII y se preparaba con todo tipo de carnes asadas y sobras. que se agregan a la salsa de tomate.

La receta que te proponemos es fácil y sacada de La cuchara de plata (Phaidon), uno de los libros de referencia para conocer a fondo la gastronomía itálica. Pero la lasaña es un plato que se presta a muchas variantes y una vez dominada la técnica podemos preparar lasañas vegetales o de pescado y mariscos.

Receta de Lasaña de carne
Ingredientes:
12 láminas de lasaña

70 gramos de parmesano rallado

Mantequilla

300 gramos de carne picada (queda más jugosa con mezcla de cerdo y ternera)

Medio vaso de vino blanco

250 gramos de tomate entero pelado

1 zanahoria

1 cebolla

Aceite de oliva

Sal

Pimienta


​Para la bechamel:

50 gramos de mantequilla

50 gramos de harina

Medio litro de leche

Sal

Pimienta

Elaboración:
1. En una cacerola calienta tres cucharadas de aceite de oliva y añade la zanahoria y la cebolla bien picadas. Cuando la cebolla esté bien dorada añadimos la carne y dejamos que también se dore.

2. Entonces echamos el vaso de vino y dejamos que se evapore.

3. Tras esto, añadimos los tomates cortados y sin pepitas, salpimentamos al gusto y dejamos cocer la salsa durante media hora.

4. Mientras se cuece la salsa boloñesa podemos hacer la bechamel. En una sartén derrite la mantequilla y añade la harina. Sin parar de remover en ningún momento ve añadiendo leche caliente hasta que la salsa comience a hervir. Añade la sal, reduce el fuego y cocina durante unos veinte minutos. Tienes que remover para que no se formen grumos. Salpimenta al gusto.

5. Pon las láminas de pasta en agua hirviendo con sal y cuando estén al dente, colócalas sobre un trapo (sepáralas para que no se peguen entre ellas).

6. Y llegamos a la parte final de la preparación, montar la lasaña. En una fuente para el horno unta la base de mantequilla y cubre la base con una primera capa de pasta. Añade una capa de salsa boloñesa, otra de bechamel, espolvorea con queso rallado, pon un poco de mantequilla y otra capa de pasta. Y así hasta terminar los ingredientes. Puedes corona la lasaña con una capa de carne, bechamel y queso, o con láminas de pasta.

7. Introduce la lasaña en el horno y cocínala a 180 grados durante media hora.

author: @whoisconihey3625
text:
Receta de mote con huesillo

Como ven les traigo una receta nuevamente y para no variar FÁCIL! un típico postre chileno que no solo sirve como postre sino a cualquier hora del día, idealmente en aquellos días calurosos en donde la sed abunda.

Cabe decir que los huesillos son duraznos deshidratados con carozo. En algunas instancias se puede sustituir por la ciruela deshidratada, pero no es de gusto masivo como el huesillo.Y el mote es semilla de trigo.

 Tiempo de Cocción: 40 mins Tiempo Total: 40 mins Porciones: 4
INGREDIENTES
250 grs de huesillos
3/4 a 1 taza de azúcar morena
1 palito de canela
1 taza de mote
INSTRUCCIONES
Remojar los huesillos en suficiente agua la noche anterior.
Al siguiente día, se ponen los huesillos con toda el agua en una olla, más el azúcar y la canela.
Se puede agregar chancaca si gustan, lo que le da el color al jugo. Otra opción es que pueden acaramelizar un poco del azúcar para agregarla cuando el jugo aún este caliente. Eso también ayuda a dejar de color el jugo. Y sino simplemente lo agregan el azúcar al momento del inicio de la cocción de los huesillos. Que puede que no quede del típico color el jugo, pero quedará igual de sabroso. Eso se los aseguro.
La cocción es de unos 30 a 40 minutos a fuego medio, hasta que los huesillos estén bien blandos. Dejar enfríar. Y luego refrigerar.
Mientras tanto se cuecen por unos 20 minutos el mote con abundante agua. Luego de la cocción hay que botar el agua con la ayuda de un colador. Dejar en una fuente que pueda ir al refrigerador. Reservar.
Una vez listo ambos ingredientes, servir bien helado en un vaso largo unas 2 a 3 cucharadas de mote, 2 huesillos y bastante jugo de los huesillos.
Mantener refrigerados el mote y los huesillos con su jugo separados.

author: @whoisconihey3625
text:
Receta de calzones rotos chilenos
Y llegó septiembre, el mes de la patria en Chile, mi país natal. Es por ello que comenzaré con una receta bien típica chilena. Ideal para la once como decimos los chilenos, o sea en otras palabras para la hora del té.
Es una masa frita, semi dulce y con un ligero toque de limón. Es bastante fácil de hacer, tan solo deben tener cuidado de lograr la consistencia de la masa y que de formar bien la forma de este dulce. Preocuparse de tener el aceite bien caliente al momento de freír, pero mantener el fuego medio a bajo para que no se le vaya a quemar el aceite.
INGREDIENTES
3 tazas de harina cernida
1 cucharada polvos de hornear
3/4 taza de azúcar flor cernida (es el azúcar en polvo)
2 cucharadas de margarina
1 huevo
2 yemas
Ralladura de 1 limón
1/2 taza de agua quizás un poco más
aceite para freír
azúcar flor para espolvorear
INSTRUCCIONES
Unir los ingredientes secos, la harina, los polvos y azúcar. Luego la ralladura de limón.
Enseguida agregar el huevo y después las yemas una a una.
Incorporar la mantequilla ablandada y unir bien la masa. Finalmente agregar agua suficiente para formar una masa homogénea.
Uslerear la masa y dejarla aproximadamente 1/2 cm de grosor. Cortar rectángulos de 10 cm por 5 cm. Luego hacer sobre ellos un corte vertical de unos 3 cm y pasar un extremo del rectángulo por este ojal.
Freír en aceite caliente, deben quedar dorados.
Escurrirlos bien y dejarlos en papel absorbente.
Finalmente espolvorear con azúcar flor.

author: @idalicelis4876
text:
Voy a seguir poniendo la misma receta una  y otra vez
1 taza de palmito, cortados en cubos pequeños
1 taza de mango, cortado en cubos
1 taza de jitomate, cortado en cubos, sin semillas
1/2 tazas de cebolla morada
1/4 tazas de chile serrano, cortado en aros
1/2 tazas de cilantro fresco, finamente picado
1 taza de jícama, cortada en cubos medianos
1/4 tazas de pepino, cortado en cubos
2 tazas de Pechuga De Pavo Virginia Fud®, picada
1 taza de jugo de limón
1/4 tazas de aceite de oliva
1 pizca de sal
1 cucharada de orégano
1 aguacate, cortado en abanicos
10 tostadas de maíz, para acompañar
Preparación
15 mins
Baja
En un bowl grande agrega los palmitos, el mango, el jitomate, la cebolla morada, el chile serrano, el cilantro, la jícama, el pepino , la Pechuga de Pavo Virginia FUD®, añade el jugo de limón, el aceite de oliva, sazona con un poco de sal y orégano al gusto.
Sirve sobre una tostada y decora con un abanico de aguacate y un poco de orégano.
Acompaña con salsa bruja y disfruta.

author: @alicia7505
text: Juana Inés de Asbaje y Ramírez; San Miguel de Nepantla, actual México, 1651 - Ciudad de México, id., 1695) Escritora mexicana, la mayor figura de las letras hispanoamericanas del siglo XVII. La influencia del barroco español, visible en su producción lírica y dramática, no llegó a oscurecer la profunda originalidad de su obra. Su espíritu inquieto y su afán de saber la llevaron a enfrentarse con los convencionalismos de su tiempo, que no veía con buenos ojos que una mujer manifestara curiosidad intelectual e independencia de pensamiento.

author: @ok_seo2830
text:
Una de las primeras medidas que tomó fue establecer una Iglesia protestante independiente de Roma, que luego evolucionaría en la actual Iglesia de Inglaterra, de la que se convirtió en la máxima autoridad.

Se esperaba que Isabel contrajera matrimonio pero, pese a varias peticiones del Parlamento, nunca lo hizo.[1]​ Se desconocen las razones para esta decisión y han sido ampliamente debatidas. A medida que Isabel fue envejeciendo, su virginidad la volvió famosa y un culto creció alrededor de ella, celebrado en retratos, desfiles y literatura de la época.

La reina se hizo cargo de un país dividido por cuestiones religiosas en la segunda mitad del siglo xvi. Durante su reinado, Inglaterra tuvo un gran esplendor cultural, con figuras como William Shakespeare y Christopher Marlowe; también fueron importantes personajes como Francis Drake y John Hawkins. Mantuvo gélidas relaciones con Felipe II de España, con quien libró una guerra que arruinó económicamente a ambos países. Su reinado de 44 años y 127 días ha sido el quinto más largo de la historia inglesa, por detrás de los de Isabel II, Victoria I, Jorge III y Eduardo III.

Una de las primeras medidas que tomó fue establecer una Iglesia protestante independiente de Roma, que luego evolucionaría en la actual Iglesia de Inglaterra, de la que se convirtió en la máxima autoridad.

Se esperaba que Isabel contrajera matrimonio pero, pese a varias peticiones del Parlamento, nunca lo hizo.[1]​ Se desconocen las razones para esta decisión y han sido ampliamente debatidas. A medida que Isabel fue envejeciendo, su virginidad la volvió famosa y un culto creció alrededor de ella, celebrado en retratos, desfiles y literatura de la época.

La reina se hizo cargo de un país dividido por cuestiones religiosas en la segunda mitad del siglo xvi. Durante su reinado, Inglaterra tuvo un gran esplendor cultural, con figuras como William Shakespeare y Christopher Marlowe; también fueron importantes personajes como Francis Drake y John Hawkins. Mantuvo gélidas relaciones con Felipe II de España, con quien libró una guerra que arruinó económicamente a ambos países. Su reinado de 44 años y 127 días ha sido el quinto más largo de la historia inglesa, por detrás de los de Isabel II, Victoria I, Jorge III y Eduardo III.

author: @riyamehta6795
text:
This song...

I don’t think SKZ realise the amount of literal lives they’ve saved with their music. 
Before I first listened to this song, I wasn’t exactly... happy. Constantly, there were so many people telling what to do, where to go, what not to do, what I should become. I was tired at just my teenage years.

I remember almost dropping my phone as this came on. I scrambled to look up the artist, and since then, I’ve not regretted clicking on this. I’ve been a STAY for just a year now, but you feel like family. Each and every stay seems so supportive and kind. 

It’s going to be difficult to convince everyone to let me walk on my own on another road, but songs like these will give me a shoulder to cry on and a friend to have when things are down.

Thank you, SKZ. Thank you, STAY. You’ve truly made me stay.

text: This is actually a song that I really relate to. Its been 4 years since I started hearing voices in my head. It tried to control everything I do. It told me to do this and to do this. It makes me overthink and makes me change my decisions so much. I try to ignore them like I cant hear them. It tries to change me so much that I lost everyone and myself. This song kinda bring a lot of comfort to me and helps me alot. This song also helped me tell my family about the voices i keep hearing and Im currently in therapy rn. Thank u skz. Im gonna start being stay now:)

author: @goosegoose1.o929
text:
*V*TINGS* :
(Apps to download... some are of v*tings and some are for promotion ads)

1. IDOL CHAMP (for w1n on "Show Champion")

2. Mwave (for w1n on "MCountdown")

3. WhosFan (for w1n on "MCountdown" too)

4. MuBeat (for w1n on "Music Core" and promotion ads)

5. TheKkings (for birthday ads, group promotion ads)

6. FanPlus (for promotion ads)

*"Voting Tutorials"*

1. *"Show Champion"*

Download Idol Champ app and follow this tutorial. Each person gets 3 votes per day. You can get red hearts by watching ads or completing missions and blue hearts by logging onto the app every day and answering quizzes.

2. *"M Countdown"*

V*ting can be done through either Mwave (website and app) and Whosfan. Download the Mwave or Whosfan app. If you have downloaded Whosfan, follow this tutorial! For Mwave, each person gets 1 v*te using one social media account. If you want to v*te for Stray Kids more, then use multiple social media accounts.

3. *"Music Core"*

Download the Mubeat app and follow this tutorial. To get heart beats, go to store and watch ads or complete missions. V*ting is unlimited and you can use multiple social media accounts for more chances to v*te. You can start collecting heart beats now, the earlier you start, the more you can accumulate for voting later...

4. *"TheKking"*

Download TheKking app.
After you sign in you’ll be directed to the homepage. From there you click the plus button next to the pink tokens.
Then you can watch ads to gain v*tes. You can watch 10 ads every hour and you get 5 tokens for each ad.Then click convert at the top and click the convert thing. You’ll be shown this convert thing and you just have to click the add point and convert. Every 10 tokens is equal to 1 vote. Then click the Group Vote then click the heart next to Stray Kids.

5. *"FanPlus"*

Download FanPlus..After you create an account you’ll be directed to the home page. From there you click v*te at the bottom.Then you’ll click free v*ting. You will watch ads. Each ad is worth 15 votes. Everyday you can watch 30 ads maximum. 

*"Pre-order Album"*

Buying albums can count on charts and music shows!

If you're from the US, consider buying from *Amazon* , *Walmart* ,
*Barnes* and *Noble* and *Choice Music LA* as it counts for both "Hanteo" and "Billboard charts" You can also buy merch along with a "digital copy" of the album.... This will count towards Billboard charts as well !!

( *Note* : Pre-orders from SubK counts for Hanteo and Gaon but do not count for Billboard..)

*"STRE@MING"*

Stre@m on Korean music platforms: 
*Genie* |  *Bugs*

Digital scores is one of the criteria for winning on music shows. 

*"Youtube Stre@ming Guide"*

Youtube vi*ws also count for music shows so it's important to accumulate as many vi*ws as possible during the time 

*"HOW TO STRE@M PROPERLY"*

1) Watch the video FROM THE FIRST UNTIL THE LAST SECOND! 

2) Watch the video in HD (720p, at least ) We are always trying to put it in higher quality. If u can afford stre@m in HD! if ur device hasn't HD or ur internet connection is low.. then 480p is allowed

3) DON'T skip, stop or rewind the video

4) The sound on your phone should be more then 50%, U can mute the sound on ur laptop and PC, but be sure that the volume on Youtube is more then 50%

5) Don't forget to leave comments and likes to not be considered as bot

6) STREAM MANUALLY! Don't use the playlists and loops when u have a free time for watching the videos on Youtube. Playlists and loops are the main reason of freezing the vi*ws for a long time..

(Remember that Youtube like to delete vi*ws..) (snake..bwkwhw)

7) DON'T USE multiple tabs or incognito mode - they are counted as SPAM and ur vi*ws will be deleted... 

8) DON'T SKIP THE ADS! They are counted as part of the video and if u will skip them.. you actually will skip the video and ur views will not counted by Youtube..

9) Don't change the speed of the video..

10) Use different browsers ( Mozilla Firefox, Opera, Google Chrome and etc ), accounts, internet connections ( Wi - Fi and mobile data ), devices ( PC, TV, phone, laptop ) for stre@ming of the videos.. these things will helping to increase the vi*ws...

11) AND NOW THERE IS THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE: you CAN'T REWATCH the same video again and again without any gaps!!!!!!!! If u will rewatch God Menu on repeat again and again.. Your vi*ws will be counted as SPAM and will be deleted....The gap among rewatching the same video should be 10 minutes or 2 other SKZ MVs in between.. 

FIGHTING STAYS 

*" Stre@ming on Naver is important "*

Stre@ming their music videos/music show performances helps in keeping Stray Kids trending on Naver. Naver is South Korea's biggest search engine. 

Soooo... Stays 

☆ Collect Red hearts on Idol Champ

☆ For mwave and whosfan you don't need to collect or save anything.. when they will start promoting their songs.. We need to directly v*te.. (you can v*te 1 time per day so it would be better to create more accounts)

☆ Collect heart beats on Mubeat ( it would be better if you'll use more than 1 account)

☆ V*te for Seungmin.. he'll have subway ads for their b-day..(Also collect hearts for Oct Line)

☆V*tes for Oct line... on FanPlus..

FIGHTING STAYS..
LET'S BE PREPARED FOR THERE NEXT COMEBACK
LET'S BREAK MORE RECORDS... LET'S GET  W1NS...

Please take care of yourself and be nice to yourself because you are worth it.

text:
The thing is, Stray Kids taught me to accept myself.
In this world where everyone is pushing the agenda of loving yourself, somehow people have forgotten to remind us that the first step towards loving yourself is accepting yourself, all your flaws, weaknesses and demons. I found Stray Kids at a time when I hated everything about me,when I couldn't accept my lost and useless self. But after meeting these beautiful people, I've learnt to accept even myself,even my weak and lost self.
So thank you Stray Kids for making me STAY.
STRAY KIDS EVERYWHERE ALL AROUND THE WORLD.
YOU MAKE ME STAY

text: Damn, this song gets me in my feels because it’s so relatable. There was a point in my life where my depression was at it’s peak. Though it still isn’t any better now it was a little worse back then. And as time went on I eventually started to hear voices, one of the scariest times in my life, it just didn’t get any better. These voices were so destructive it was the worst. So whenever I hear Chan’s “There’s so many voices” it just sends chills down my spine.

author: @Mari-hm7vc
text: I discovered Stray Kids a few weeks ago. A while ago, I was in the midst of a crisis, and this song started playing (I was listening to music to try to distract me) and then I started to calm down; I think something like this has never happened to me before; I found it incredible. Although I did not know very well what the lyrics of the song said, it reached me, and it reached me a lot. Just minutes before, a very, very strong feeling had come to me, that of doing you know what, but Stray Kids, this song, saved me. Literal. As "cheesy" as it sounds. I never imagined it would happen to me. Stray Kids have a place in my heart from now on. Even though they won't read this, I just wanted to leave it here.

author: @andthatsalongassride9587
text:
OK I know this sounds a bit cringe but, I had like a small panic attack once, it isn't anything like that what most people have been through and I feel kinda dumb writing this. It was on a normal day in my class, the teacher was sick or something I don't remember but  my class was so loud. Everything was booming and I couldn't help myself it reminded me of all  the times my parents had fighted and I couldn't do anything, I at some point had crouched down under my table, my head in my knees with my best friend beside me trying to comfort me. I don't clearly k ow why I had a panic attack at that point but I know there were voices haunting me. It was crazy and at the point I just wanted it to stop. Since then I hold great respect for the people that have to go through something like that everyday.

I hope everyone of you is alright, please stay healthy and remember no matter how dark the situation is there is always light even though you don't see this at first....

author: @Tyler_Not_Taylor
text:
Stray Kids - “Voices” Analysis
Overview: 
Overall very nice song, no reliance on autotune, can’t hear any of it if it was used
Strong reliance on synth and bass, but acoustic guitar mainly used for rap section and transition, or by itself
“Ah” sound effect sparingly used in the background
Bass singer, when used, creates a f a t triple octave harmony
Choreography is godly, synchronized with music and beat
When rap sections are on, only shows one or two members, while in chorus sections, uses multiple dancers
Member singing at 1:30 is my favorite, his voice is much more r o b u s t
Intro:
Bass progression up and down F chord
Voice moving up and down F chord, alternating with bass for inverse harmony
Breathing sound effect emulates the theme of voices
Tempo ~ 80 BPM, 4/4 time
Rap Break:
Shift to ~ 140 BPM, shifts to cut time
Acoustic Guitar introduced into the background
Usage of synth classic dubstep in replacement of bass progression
Rapper moves in sync with chord progression, creating open harmony
Bass becomes stronger, to help reinforce synth
Transition Out: 
Slap synth doubles, chord begins to shift to augmented-major
Scoop up to perfect octave right before Chorus
Introduction to multiple English lyrics
Chorus: 
Background soprano octave reinforces open harmony, moving inversely from 8 - 7 - 6, alternating to 8 - 7 - 4, creating inverse and open harmony
Constant Synth beat repeated
“Voices” lyric becomes main repeated line
Concentrated lyrics at the end speed up the tempo, then stop when arriving at transition
Echo used for high voices, a good alternative to reverb
Transition Out:
2 new singer introduced, drastically changes tone because of the removal of echo
New lyrics thrown in but then shifts back to casual transition
Chorus: 
Almost the same as before, but new singers added
Stronger echo
“Break free from the voices” line has removed echo, to symbolize the breaking away
Raindrop oscillating effect added in 
Drums are stronger
Transition Out:
Pretty much the same, reduced tempo
Many more English lyrics added to reinforce the central idea of the song
Rap Break:
Unique in that it shifts from person to person when rapping
Voice introduced in Transition Out gets added into the rap
Rapping stretches and compresses tempo
Synth Drop:
Big choreography moment
Synth becomes exposed, moving up and down 1 and 3 chords
Synth begins to scoop, unlike earlier
“Voices” line is emphasized in the background, echo is almost tripled
Ending:
Choreography becomes more and more centered towards the ground, with only 3 remaining standing at the end
Voice sound effect reintroduced from the beginning
R A T I N G : 9.5, very n i c e

author: @fairyqis0311
text:
That one time, there was butterflies in my stomach when i went for a drama audition for school. I was scared, scared of people's judgements, scared if im not doing well, scared if im lacking and cant meet the judges expectations, insecurities and that's really haunt me. But i keep playing this song in my head, as it says "break free from the voices in my head" and that's truly help a lot!  I overcomed it and somehow i felt proud of myself! Too bad, I didn't win the audition but i don't feel regret or sad at all, I think it's my first time not listening to those bad 'voices' and i told myself "do as you practiced without regret and give it all out". Then, turned out that i didn't win, rather than feeling sad i feel happy instead bcs i managed to ignore those 'voices'! 

THANKS FOR THOSE WHO READ THIS, I TRULY APPRECIATE IT! AND THANKS TO STRAY KIDS, I GOT TO OVERCOME MY FEAR ❤❤😘

author: @bratz736
text:
*Ngl this song gives me a weird vibe at **0:01**. It also kinda gives me a headache (in a good way) and this song makes me cry cuz I feel their pain. Idk if i can say i'm depressed but eh. I've always had this feeling that my father never loved me. He never took care of me when I was child. I rarely see him on Sundays and if i do, we either hang out with his friends. And I'm done wasting my tears for him. People at my school make fun of me cuz my mom has tattoos and says that i'm not Christian even tho I am. I have/had bitchy friends who judged me for who i am (and fake friends). Boys at my school call me gay and "mistake" me as a boy even tho I'm a girl. This song just calms me down and lets my emotions out since I have nobody to talk to. (and other SKZ songs) Worst part is that I was crying typing this.*








*i just wanna be myself*

author: @napofeternity3477
text:
You're tired. You've been walking in this endless dark room for hours. Days. You're weak, and walk on shattered glass. You haven't stopped walking, yet you feel no pain as the shards rip you apart. There's a slight echo in the distance, so dim that you can't tell what it says, yet so loud that you can't hear anything, not even yourself. You feel you've become an object in this world, and the pain you feel matters nothing. Because no matter what you feel inside, you're always wrong.
This isn't true. Every person has a beautiful soul filled with the passion of a million stars. Follow your dreams.

author: @rianadn2150
text:
This makes me cry every time. Ive had this voice in my head for as long as I can remember and was so great they made this song addressing it. Every time I feel tired of being ‘strange’ or ‘irregular’ (some people said), I come back here to listen to this. This voice I have had done so many awful things to me and those around me. I know it’s kind of late, but it was one of the many things that helped me reach out to my school counsellor. I’m just so happy coming back and listening to this song again, knowing I can turn to my counsellor and songs like this. 

Sorry this is all over the place. I’m just overwhelmed
 ｡ﾟ(ﾟ´ω`ﾟ)ﾟ｡

author: @Hannahpaj
text: When I discovered them I was in a bad place, but one day as I was listening to one of my fav songs a little braver I saw everyone saying Felix fav song! And I was like who’s Felix? So I typed him in and found skz. I listened to my pace and at first didn’t like it, ( now I love it lol ) it was new to me and I wasn’t sure how to feel about them, but I decided to listen to this song and it changed my life, I felt that they were singing to me. Long story short I’ve been a stay for over a year, Thank you stray kids if it weren’t for this song I wouldn’t be here, they got me through the hardest time of my life. They’re gonna save lots more lives with songs like this. Stray kids fighting!

author: @SleepEludesMe647
text:
It needs to be said: Woojin, your opening here was what made me interested in Stray Kids. I’ll always say that M.I.A is my favourite track and MV, that I AM You is the title track that meant the most to me, and that Tomorrow, Today is my favourite SKZ PLAYER. You did so well in those, maybe I appreciated them all the more because I could hear more from you, the one who, in those make-it-or-break-it seconds for someone to judge if a song that seems to outside of their comfort zone, if a group that seems to be outside their preferred genres and styles, could move and awe me with their music. I have you to thank for opening the world of Stray Kids to me, and I’ll always come back here to remember what that was like. 

I don’t know what you’re going through right now, only that it can’t have been easy, but I will do what I can to support you wherever you may go. We are proud to have been there to watch you on your journey with Stray Kids. Thank you for everything you have done for us, and for them. #ThankYouWoojin

author: @kathy_zvd
text:
pelo que eu entendi ( minha teoria)
As vozes são as opiniões das pessoas e o que elas fazem com a nossa cabeça, influenciando nas nossas decisões. "Parem, vozes que me julgam" em 1.21 
No MV ele diz que ele quer se livrar das vozes e que toda essas vozes o sufocam, etc...
Na minha opinião essa musica mostra para as Stay que as pessoas querem "fazer" a nossa cabeça querendo com que a gente não escolha o que realmente nós queremos, porém quando eles falam no refrão "Vou me libertar das vozes deles" ele meio que mostra que podemos fazer a nossas escolhas sozinhos e que as vezes algumas opiniões não devem ser seguidas se não são de nosso agrado! 
POXA ISSO  TEM QUE SER VALORIZADO MUITO MAIS MANO!!!!!! AMO STRAY KIDS ,_,

author: @SilentxForever
text:
It just hurts because there are so many people telling me what to do with my life. I don't know what to do because I don't even know what I WANT.
I feel so unmotivated and useless now because of it. I was supposed to be the one that had a set future. And here it is now, in crumbles because people voiced their own wishes.
I'm stagnant. Not doing anything because I don't want to disappoint anybody, but most importantly, myself. I don't want to regret my choice, so I don't choose anything.
I don't think the voices will leave my head anytime soon.
My head hurts.

author: @paigieinu1988
text: the first time i listened to this song was maybe at the start of this year. i’ve read many comments from people saying that they suffer from things like anxiety and depression, like me, who suffers from anxiety, but i never found much comfort in that. despite knowing i wasn’t the only one, those people didn’t know me, i didn’t know them so it felt just as lonely. stray kids are even further away than that, yet this song made me feel so emotional, and for the first time i didn’t feel so empty and on the edge. they care. they know how it feels. they are there for you. i started to put myself in those people’s shoes, and even though i still didn’t know them, i think i finally understood how hard it is to convey your emotions and feelings. i’ve never been more proud to be in a fandom, i’m still amazed at how emotional i felt. honestly, i don’t think i’ll ever get over my anxiety, but now i think i can cope with it better. to all those people i still don’t know, but understand a little better: thank you, and i hope you are doing well. <3 this video is a little older, but i just wanted to get this off my chest :)

author: @namgan_S3
text:
Sometimes you need to close your ears and trust your heart to walk towards your own path... No matter what parents, friends, or other people tell you how you are supposed to live in order to succeed in life, even if it would risk you to leave everything behind, you need to follow your dream and passion...


I'm in nursing school right now and the only reason why I'm in nursing school is to have a stable job... I tried to convince myself that nursing is meaningful job that helps other people but to be honest, my motivation was not "helping other people," but "making a living." I was scared to follow my dream and study what I really want to study because I thought it would be very financially insecure... But I JUST CANNOT DO IT JUST TO MAKE A LIVING... Isn't it life more than making a living?


...and there are so many VOICES in my head... and staring eyes...

author: @adrianna9678
text:
A Long Message About How K-Pop Affected My Life:
* This goes to everyone that thinks I'm weird for liking K-Pop, you guys have no idea how much K-Pop affected my life. Let's talk about the time before I discovered, I was really depressed, had so much insecurities about myself and etc. I was bullied in elementary and Abused at home, to made it worse for me, my papa was suffering from a type of lung cancer, all at the age of 5. I've been suicidal at the age of 8 till the age of 13. I'm 14 right now. But one day I've discovered K-Pop by accident, it was bts but then I started to open up to more groups. On the other hand, K-Pop/Groups has thought me so much then any other genre or artist had. Some of their songs thought me how to love myself, appreciate others and what I have, adore the small things in life, friendship is one of the most powerful things a human can ever had, how to be mature, how to get over my depression, that its alright to have insecurities ans that everyone has their flaws and that I'm not alone, I should reach out for help and that no one is gonna judge me for asking for help. Like this song "Voices" "get the voice out of my head" I could relate to that on a whole another level its crazy.. but eventually I did learn how to get the voices out of my head. Thanks to K-Pop I wouldn't probably be here right now. Thank You. *

author: @jackybaduria806
text:
For me, whenever I listen to this song, it always reminds me of how someone is speaking to us, someone bad, someone who wants to ruin our life, someone who wants to destroy everything about us. And that is the devil. Whenever there is something you shouldn't be doing, maybe something that's really bad, or maybe a temptation to just do that thing, then that's the devil's voice. That means you are listening to the devil's voice. Even giving up on something was because of the devil. Try to listen to the Lord and he will help you find your way out. Something good will come out of that. And here is Stray Kids always reminding us to keep going no matter how hard it is, and no matter what struggles you may have to face. Remember there is no success without struggles, so face it. If you have the passion to achieve something, do it. Don't give up. Don't let the devil win. That won't do no good. Don't rush. Just keep it at your own pace. It's better to let yourself gradually grow rather than succeeding right away. So have patience. In your own pace, you can learn new things and improve yourself more. To the 1% people reading this, never give up. Don't rush. Just go on your own pace. One day you will reach your goal:) I believe in you all! I love you SKZ & STAY❤

Thank you so much, Stray Kids, for always comforting us with these deep and meaningful lyrics. Something you are going through, that's what you tell in your songs. You tell your story through your music. We know what you're going through. That's struggles and us STAYs can really relate to you guys. These songs really help us through whatever we're going through and I just want to give you all my gratitude back to you! I appreciate it so much! Facing similar issues, we can just, you know, figure it out together, right? We can work together as a team, right? We can do everything together! We can help each other whenever we need it. STAY & SKZ is the best! We are not a fandom, we are a family❤

_"You know, whenever you guys are having a hard time, feel depressed, or got a lot on your mind, just wanna say that, you know, it's always ok to come to us. Come to me, come to Stray Kids and tell us how you feel. Tell us what you're feeling. Cause, you know, we have ears to listen to. We will listen to you guys. And no matter what, we will try to help out with what you're going through. Because I think that's one thing that everyone in Stray Kids can agree on. We will always try to fix you guys. So, if you guys have anything, you know, come find us. We'll help you out."_ — Bang Chan (2019 April 14)❤

*Bang Chan, Kim Woojin, Lee Minho, Seo Changbin, Hwang Hyunjin, Han Jisung, Lee Felix, Kim Seungmin, Yang Jeongin:*
_"You know, whenever you guys are having a hard time, feel depressed, or got a lot on your mind, just wanna say that, you know, it's always ok to come to us. Come to me, come to STAY and tell us how you feel. Remember we are always here to try our best to help you guys through whatever you're going through. We will always be there for you guys no matter happens. We will try our best to try to fix you guys. Just tell us, you know, we'll always be here to help, remember that._ — STAY❤

*_I love you SKZ & STAY❤_*
*_Let's keep fighting together!_*
*_Let's keep flying high together!_*
*_Let's keep cherishing every moment of our lives together!_* 
*_SKZ & STAY Fighting💪_*

I know what they are referring to with the song, it talks about that we do not have to give importance to the voices, to those who are in our heads, that happened to me in sixty degrees, I felt that I had a demon in my head, I did not in peace, but then I went to a church meeting that my cousin invited me to, and that was when everything changed. but, later it distracts me (with the BTS) and I went away, but now I'm going back to the same path, because the distraction led me to know God again, I hope you hear this song in those times.

a and by ciero I saw some of you with the remerade Argentina in one of your presents ... will someday come to my country? ... I do not know.

author: @momoabels6898
text: I feel like what sets them apart from so many other groups is the fact they write their own lyrics about things that are important to them. Not only do they put so much effort into all their performances but the fact they write their songs about things that matter to them or in order to help others puts so much more emotion and passion into them. It’s amazing. And not to compare them, but they only other group who has ever been able to make me cry like this through their music is BTS. And I feel like that says something. Again I’m not trying to compare them to BTS bc every group is different. But I feel like the fact they write about things that are important to them helps sooo much. I’m sure it’s easy for someone to write a song about something fun and whatever, but it’s harder and more emotional to write a song about topics usually that no one is willing to address. And to make it feel so sincere, you know they’ve had to have gone through it too.

I always like Voices, put specially today it was like and oasis in the desert. Every minute of every day I hear a different opinion of what should I do, how, when, where of every thing I what to do, I'm doing, I will do or about what I didn't do and I just break, it was overwhelming and the only thing that calm me was this song. 
I felt that I wasn't alone, that I'm not the only one that I'm passing through this and that I can overcome this fase of my life. 
So, thank you Stray Kids, for always knowing what to say even if you are in the other side of the world 💕

author: @almostidioticgirl
text: Am I the only one who think that this is Stray Kids' best song from pre-debut until Miroh? This song just gives me chills from the get-go, the intro is strumming my heartstrings with sadness. There are just so many feelings in this song, in their choreo, in how they sing it. How Woojin opened the song with despair, then Changbin exploded with frustration, Chan screaming to break out, the pain for not being able to do so in Felix's strained voice, and Lee Know's defeated sigh. They even fell on their knees at his part. At the end Chan and Woojin are no longer screaming, but it's like a desperate plea, and closed by Felix's quiet surrender. The progress of this song is so emotionally draining, and I love it so much. The only other song I've heard that brought me through the journey of feelings is Day6's I Need Somebody. Of course I feel other songs too, but it usually just one kind of feeling. The two songs though, they're epic 😍

author: @atinymoon
text:
This was the song that made me stan these beautiful biscuits.
The lyrics hit me so hard since I got them basically in two ways. 
First is that I was bullied really badly for 4 years and people talked a lot bad stuff about me. Rumors, saying mean things, sending mean messages... It made me stop hearing my own voice. All I heard, were the disrespectful and mean things that others told to me.
Then the second way is that, after those 4 years, my own mind started to tell me all these things. I was so lost and couldn't hear the voice inside of me, the encouraging and sweet things all disappeared. Still, to this day I fight with my own self, but this song makes me feel like I'm not alone.
So stay, who are struggling, you're not alone. We have each other and we have Stray Kids.

author: @abigailroberts6925
text:
I don't get how people can dislike this song or the video,their literally talking about serious mental health issues like depression,anxiety etc. This is one of their more serious songs with a serious message and meaning behind it. They know that a lot of their fans have mental illnesses and their saying to just not worry about the voices in your head and that the bad times are just bad times and that there is always light at the end of the tunnel and you will get through it if you don't give up. Their there to help you get through those bad times through their music as channie always says. Stray Kids are always trying to be funny and caring for their fans even though we all know they go through these rough patches as well whether it's by individually or as a team. They are so caring,kind,grateful and lovely to their fans because were the same to them and they know that we love them to. I just really wish people would look at the lyrics and listen to the way there singing some of there parts because this is a message they really wanted to get across to all their fans that might be going through a rough patch or a rough time in their life 

I'm so sorry that this was so long and I'm grateful to anyone who read it all I just want people to see past their good looks and music videos to see the true meaning behind their music 
STAY forever 
Stray Kids fighting

author: @queenz2415
text: Y'know sometimes I feel like pounding my head into a wall because of how angry I get and how hard things get. My art has started deteriorating because I stopped for a long time and I still love art so much. Writing used to be my favorite too but I barely do that anymore either. All of this plus school and having to accept the fact that I'm growing up and will have to leave my parents in like two years always leaves me upset and angry. Knowing how short time is and how little time there is really gets me down. I feel like I've got the message wrong in this song but whenever I listen to it I feel like it's speaking to me. Like it understands everything that frustrates and upsets me and tells me to put it all behind me and love being myself. Thank you Stray Kidz :')

author: @diniwiradinata
text: Ok yes, my depression has told me several stuff like 'you don't matter.' 'no one loves you' 'theyll never be able to help you, so why reach out for help?' and stuff like that, but I feel like this song represents my intrusive thoughts more. I really don't want to describe them, but if I could find the best way to describe how I _feel_ about them is just helplessnes. I'm drowning in all the voices and I just feel so helpless, so weak, so tired. Their dance; where they sorta bend down on one knee, represents how I feel. Just tired. As if I've been knocked down. And when chan helplessly and tiredly said 'theres so many voices', I felt that too. If I could say something in the middle of my intrusive thoughts, it'll probably be that. All I can say is that I'm very thankful that stray kids made this song and reached out to me and many other people. Stray kids fighting~!

author: @jeonihyun
text: I really love this song, next to School Life. This song was so relatable, I always get hurt Everytime I hear judgemental, or hurtful words. I feel like I was worthless, I didn't have any power to fight these voices I kept on hearing, I try with saying "not all people are perfect, so do I." But I can't, I force myself to ignore these voices I hear about myself, but I can't. It so useless if I ignore, or even if I cover my ears, because its on my mind now, I overthink it. But with this song, I loved it. It helped me be strong again, thank you stray kids. 💓

text:
Listening to this song lightens up my mood a bit. I'm just so frustrated by everyone around me who expects me to live up to their expectations, be a flawless student, have excellent grades, get a scholarship (which I'm trying to get but haven't receive a response to my application in weeks). I'm sick of it all. Not to mention i've been feeling burned out and my grades are starting to get average. My principal also nags a lot because she is disappointed with our scores and is afraid that it'll ruin our school's reputation. My whole family is also rooting for me to get a scholarship and i feel burdened. I just want to survive in this competitive society and get a decent college and job (-_-メ)

text:
"is in Spanish and English"      "esta en español e ingles"
they need to be more recognized not only because they are beautiful but because of the themes of their songs, I know that they are not the only ones that talk about this topic because there can be many more kpop groups that talk about it but that does not mean that we have to compare them because even though the groups have the same concept everyone has their own shine for that and many more things I do not think that stray kids should be compared with another group being so they should receive much more attention than that they currently have because they deserve it since the chan's sleeplessness should not be in vain, jisung has opened up with us telling us all the problems he suffered in order to debut, jeongin told us that he often pretends to smile so we do not worry by him, hyunjin is often frustrated and feels that he is not handsome enough to be considered visual or that he is not a good rapper, since it is not so, felix who arrived from australia to the same He chan to pursue his dream has been a long time since he sees his family, Minho feels very pressured by being the main dancer and that is why when he does not step out he ends up very frustrated, changbin like chan and jisung has I spent many sleepless nights to write a song and get it perfect, woojin had to go through training for many companies until I could find one in which I could debut as I never felt it was very good and last but not least seungmin have an angelical voice and like everyone feels that it can not only that in my opinion I feel that it does not show much and for this many more things we should give to stray kids even if it is a prize in the musical shows although we know that they deserve more for everything the effort they put in and well I think I have nothing more to say, I hope, and if you took the time to read it, I'll give it to you. ¡Stray kids is where you stay!

author: @Alex-vs5dh
text:
After about 2 years of Seventeen being my ultimate group, I think Stray Kids have replaced them. 

Their music calms me down or makes me just smile and want to dance (depends on the song) and every single member is incredible in their own way. They all make me feel happy and incredibly loved, even if I’ve never met them. 


Being Chan biased, his live-streams started at a time when I couldn’t have needed them more. Between college, money problems, a breakup and stressing about my sister, my mental health went downhill quickly and nothing was helping. However his live-streams have honestly helped me so much. just have a short period of time every week where I can interact with others dealing with similar issues, and an incredibly kind soul with a fantastic music taste helps me so much. I enjoy just knowing I’m connected to so many different people who are all inspired by the same people I am. 

Thank you Stray Kids, for giving us such incredible music and making us feel like everything will be ok. 

And thank you to all the other Stay’s! Everyone I’ve talked to has been so kind and I can’t thank you enough. I am so proud to be part of this incredible family

author: @channiesroom5825
text:
My best friend recently got in a car accident and unfortunately did not survive the crash. Its devastating, and there's some vital piece of me missing without him here with me but this music, Stray Kids music is helping me through it. I don't want to be one of those who write depressing comments but I'm gonna do it just once because its weighing on my mind


3:40 am in the morning and my friend died. I was talking to him like 30 minutes before - its been about 2 weeks and constantly there are voices in the back of my head telling me that there was something I could have done, I left him on read cuz I fell asleep-if I hadn't could I have done something? Could he still be here? The voices whisper his name all the time and everything reminds me of him somehow, Chan's part when he says 'There's so many voices' so brokenly speaks so many volumes its uncanny - this song, it means something to me, to everyone - it help to distract me, to give me hope and reassure me its not the end of everything


I am glad to be a Stay. I am glad to have Stray Kids with me, giving me encouragement and songs that speak to me on levels I have never experienced before. It is hard right now, but thanks to them I know I will get through it. 
Thank you Stray Kids, you make us Stay<3

author: @Faith-pp2mm
text:
Voices is such a deep song that deserves so much more appreciation.
The emotion in Chan’s “There’s so many voices” really hits hard. I think we all struggle with thoughts or voices in our minds saying “I’m not good enough, I’m not worthy enough, I’m annoying, unloved, the list goes on. It’s so so hard to fight those voices, and sometimes they win. Hyunjin’s line, “at some point I started to hear those nagging sounds only” really connected with me. After so long of hearing those voices it comes to the point where those negative and destructive thoughts are the only thing you can hear no matter how hard you try to tell yourself they aren’t true. To me, this song is a reminder to keep fighting, and even if you lose once to continue rejecting those thoughts. No matter how well we do, we’ll have times where those voices will come rushing back, but one day I’m sure we’ll be able to break free from those voices. I’m so thankful to Stray Kids for making music like this, and I’m so thankful to part of the amazing kingdom that is STAY💖

author: @annalynefrazer4330
text: I commented something in My Pace and I thought I should just say this here too after a reccomendation. I want to say how powerful and meaningful this song is for me because I've been struggling and drowning in voices I never wished for and no one seems to understand. This song not only depicted how I feel perfectly, but it also gave me encouragement towards the end. I am not a stay but after seeing the meaning behind theirs songs, I feel like I really can stay. In a world where you can feel really alone, music can embrace and accompany you. Stay Kids-- their music became that embrace I've been longing for and I feel like they're able to voice out things I can only dream of saying. I hope they get more recognition. I hope more people realise how powerful these songs are-- how talented these boys are.

author: @shaniaturner7571
text:
0:15, 0:59, 1:54, 2:07 {white shirt, tan pants} *Kim Woojin* [stage name: Woojin] (main vocalist, underrated vocals loves his chicken, nickname is bear, '97 liner, oldest)
0:28, 2:22, 2:48 {white shirt, tan jacket, brown pants} *Seo Changbin* [stage name: Changbin] (main rapper, vocalist, producer, 1/3 of 3RACHA who writes, composes, and produces Stray Kids' music [was formed in 2013], '99 liner)
0:40, 1:03, 2:10 {white shirt, pants, jacket, headband} *Kim Seungmin* [stage name: Seungmin] (lead vocalist, vocals are pure sunshine, nickname is puppy because of his facial features, '00 liner)
0:45, 1:09, 1:52, 2:15 {white shirt, speckled black jacket} *Lee Felix/Yongbok* [stage name: Felix] (lead dancer, lead rapper, don't underestimate his vocals, half of the Aussie line, was born in Sydney Australia but has Korean parents, '00 liner)
0:48, 1:16, 1:34, 2:23, 2:40 {brown short sleeves on top of white long sleeves with blue spots, brown shorts, blonde} *Han Jisung* [stage name: Han] (main rapper, lead vocalist, producer, 1/3 of 3RACHA, multitalented king, nickname is squirrel because of his facial features and the fact he stuffs his cheeks with food when he eats, '00 liner)
0:52, 2:00, 2:50 {white short sleeves, black speckled pants} *Bang Chan/Chris* [stage name: Chan] (leader, lead vocalist, lead dancer, rapper, producer, last member of 3RACHA, other half of the Aussie line, moved to Australia when he was young, loves the other members and fans very much, '97 liner)
0:55, 1:48, 2:04 (standing in middle) {greyish/greenish long sleeves, white pants} *Yang Jeongin* [stage name: I.N.] (vocalist, maknae, a literal baby, used to have braces but recently had them removed, nickname is fox, '01 liner)
1:05, 1:11, 1:21, 2:19 {white long sleeves, black vest, striped pants} *Hwang Hyunjin* [stage name: Hyunjin] (main dancer, lead rapper, visual, can be cute and rude, sometimes at the same time, '00 liner)
2:26 {white long sleeves, black speckled with white jacket, black pants with chain on the left hip} *Lee Minho* [stage name: Lee Know, sometimes shortened to Lino] (main dancer, vocalist, rapper, was a backup dancer with BTS on their Wings Trilogy tour, '98 liner)

author: @madlala6618
text: hello stays! i would like to bring attention to another wonderful stay, isaac. his channel is isaacskz (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCz9eswAEaSn6VqubtSBMatg) his dream was to be the best stray kids editing account, and sadly he passed away from a brain tumour. however, us stays want to remember him and thank him for all the hard work, so if you can please watch his videos! they're truly amazing and you won't regret it. we are trying to spread love for him! you can check out #youdidwellisaac, #isaacandministaystrong, #skzxisaac on IG, and you will see he means so much to us. he worked very hard to edit for us. he used to have an instagram fan account, but it is now deleted. the recent videos on his channel also has his last words to us and his sister (@forhanjisung)'s letter for us. thank you for reading <3 he always said he's literally GIVING the edits for us, and it would mean a lot to isaac if we were able to enjoy them! so i'd like stays who havent seen them to check them out! he also said to support each other and the boys and that's the most precious part about isaac! please read his letter https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tc8xGGRHDFk (and here is his sisters: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XrUn7WGO-w0)

author: @thegoinggmerry
text:
This song is really something I can relate to. To hear Chan say "There's so many voices", almost helpless and defeated, kills me. I'm going through really tough times at my house and I constantly feel so much stress and pressure that it makes me paranoid. My situation at my small apartment with my family is confusing. Not to mention that I'm bisexual and my grandparents are homophobic. I always felt lost and without purpose and it hurts. It hurts so badly, to have a voice in the back of your head telling you that you're not loved. That you're hideous. That you're a failure. That your friends think that you're annoying. Oh, and I don't blame my friend for thinking this way, but one of my friends does think that. So music like this is really moving for me. Its like the glue that holds my broken and sometimes useless thoughts together. Thanks to the people who actually read this whole thing btw please don't hurt yourself. Please don't starve yourself. Don't hate yourself. Don't convince yourself that you don't matter like I have. Have an amazing day ^^

Edit: WHOA I never thought that one of my comments would become so popular thank you for liking my comment ^^
Another edit: oml y'all are so supportive ty so much y'all

author: @majal3684
text:
dear woojin, hyunjin, chan, jeongin, minho, jisung, changbin, felix and seungmin,
for the 1% chance that you're gonna read this one day, i just want to tell you that i cried when i listened to this.

i was an army for 2 years already and i didn't think i could ever feel as much love towards an artist like i feel towards bts, just because their music is healing, real and i can relate to them. but thanks to one of my best friends she said i should listen to get cool and n/s because she liked these songs at that time. so i listened to them. i really liked get cool but i wasn't that much into n/s. i listened to my pace before but i didn't listened to the lyrics so i didn't really cared about it. but 11 days ago, it was the 26th december 2018. i was alone at home and began to watch some videos. i immediately fell in love with all of you. I wanted to know more, so i watched several guide videos and after one hour i knew your names xddd then i watched so many mvs and guides that day late into the night. i listened to your music on spotify and the next day i immediately printed photos of you for my kpop journal. only two days after stanning you, you already were my ult group with bts and i've been binging your vids since then. I just want to thank you for healing with your music, for helping people who are struggling, for making such inspirational music and for being the persons who you are. i never ever would've thought to fall in love with a kpop group once again like with bts 2 years ago, but it happened and i'm so thankful for that and i will love you forever even when i haven't walked the path with you together from the very beginning.

author: @aarenjun8505
text: okay, i know that they didn't write this song about ocd, but i can really relate to every word in this song. constantly, there are voices in my head; not the schizophrenia type, i can't hear other people. but it's my own voice, commanding me like a lifeless puppet. lifeless, because, i don't care about my health. don't eat, even if you're losing weight and it's scaring you that you can see your ribs, even in dim light. whisper a set of fragile words, like a charm, or your mom will be dead by morning. just like your dad. *don't* even think about going to that party; what if someone gets sick? don't call school sick. you aren't sick, you're just scared. like the coward you are. or maybe you are sick. maybe you need a mental facility, you nut job. who gets this scared? who touches each side of the wall so it'll feel right? who uses clorox wipes to wash their phone off every day? who can't listen to the tv unless the volume is on a multiple of five? _me. i do._ that's right. you're just crazy. _crazy?_ *crazy.*

author: @laratoya7088
text:
i can relate far too much to this song and i can tell im about to do the tmi thing but ill be brief
i am a sufferer from depression. it sucks, yeah, and i still have it. ive had it since i was 8 and am now almost sixteen. ive had ups and downs, and am slowly recovering but i do have some i guess side effects from the deeper parts of it. i reached one of the lowest points about 2 years ago now, and ever since ive experienced almost daily intrusive thoughts id guess youd call them - not exactly words as such, but pressing voicelike sounds in my head that i cant get to go away and can come at random times. when i have an episode like this, it can be extremely difficult for me to concentrate and i often have to try and force my mind to move onto another train of thought which can take any length of time from ten minutes to an hour. 
at other times there are distinguishable words, which give the vibe of basically the world being a hellhole and no one would miss me or alternatively more anxiety based e.g. everythings going to slow, speed uo, you cant help it etc.
but yeah i just relate a lot to this song as it is a constant battle with the voices in my head i guess. 
if you struggle with anything similar, i often find that listening to music can help, or thinking about your favourite movie. i sometimes stop what im doing and as im quite a musical person, pick a random song and try to work out the time signature and i do that until i can fully focus. not the most effective but it will go away on its own

wow that wasnt as brief as i thought itd be sorry 😂

author: @am_rima
text:
How I fell in love to this song...

I was washing the dishes as usual, at night, and I was playing Hellevator first and literally jamming with my earbuds and my soapy hands AND then this song started playing so I was like 

“HOLD UP. WAIT” *
frantically rinsing my hands and wiping them dry*
//song continues to play//
“I said WAAAAIT”
*pulls out my phone from my hoodie pocket*
“BRUHHHHH. NAHHH. THIS SONG. NAHHHH 🙊 “

Like bruh this song is hella good and like always everything is hella amazing — dances, rapping, singing and like UGGHH YASS.

And so I was like..
*pauses the mv*
“My dishes can wait, but my STRAYKIDS cannot”
*WATCHES THE WHOLE MV*

Me : Idk why but I wanna cry now.. 😭💞

author: @meg82133
text:
I’m really proud of them.. they know about what’s happening around the world and that’s why all their songs are dark. 
  For example, Hellevator. Not only do I really like the tune, I also really understood the meaning and lyrics of the songs. 
  They’re deep.. and when I finally understood their songs, I seriously wanted to cry because of the meaning. 
  At first I preferred BTS because I didn’t know much about Stray Kids and thought that BTS’ songs were much happier and lighter. 
  But after becoming a true STAY, I understood everything, why their songs were so dark and sounded unhappy(except for Awkward Silence of course). 
  Now I like both Stray Kids and BTS equally. ❤️I hope all KPOP groups will stay strong and united and happy forever.❤️
  And I’m sorry this was so long. It actually could be longer but I decided to compress everything together. 
  New STAYS, please love our boys with all of your heart. Don’t just look at their faces and listen to their songs. Do understand..

author: @idkhwan2632
text:
The masks hit me hard
To me it feels like, 
Like People Can Still hear you talk but, they can't hear the trapped crys for help you beg for

And you feel like, you can't 
Speak up for yourself
That's why it hit me hard
Not to mention i Have Anxiety and Mild Depression
But don't worry 
I didnt hurt myself in a month!! :D
I am not completely happy but im getting there
I still suffer from anxiety and slight insecurity 
But i should be fine
Dont worry about me
Worry about yourself 
Beacsue you are worth it!
You can kick Depressions Butt!!
And that's all I have to say

I love You Stray Kids
You helped me fight and get through this
Although you may not read this, the lyrics are meaningful and poweful
Thank You 
💓Thank You So Much💕
Peace💙

To our new *STAYs* , We have these rules we want you to know and follow:
1 *JYPnation is one. I don't make the rules. Bang Chan said it himself that you can't stan them if you hate **_TWICE_** . **_GOT7_** Jinyoung is Hyunjin's role model, Seungmin is a **_MYDAY_** , They are all TWICE's fanboys especially Felix and love to dance to their songs. They respect **_2PM_** so much especially BangChan. And a lot more interactions with other JYP artists is about to happen* . 

2. *We don't sexualize these kids. even if most of them are 18 and older they are still KIDS. Please their names says it too* .

3. *NEVER and Don't participate in FANWARS. We don't attack we defend. We respect all artists. If ever trolls come and spread hate, reply with with respect and love, that would make them shut up. Our boys are humble and respectful and they are our role models so be like them. Or just report their comments. Or just tell them to better go and stream their fave's m/v* 

4. *We stan talent. We stan 9 individuals in this group. 9 or None. Never 8, never 7, never 6, never 5, never 4, never 3, never 2, NEVER 1. We stan a family* . 

5. *STAY don't STRAY* . 

Comment what I missed. I love *_STRAY KIDS_* and you, *_STAYs_* .

text:
To our new stays
We have these rules we want you to know and follow:
1. JYPnation is one. I don't make the rules. Bang Chan said it himself that you can't stan them if you hate Twice. Got7 Jinyoung is Hyunjin's role model, Seungmin is a myday, They are all twice's fanboys especially Felix and love to dance to their songs. They respect 2pm so much especially BangChan. And a lot more interactions with other Jyp artists is about to happen. (You don't have to stan their seniors, what's important is you give respect.)
2. We don't sexualize these kids. even if most of them are 18 and older. Please their names says it too. Think about it, they might be adults now in your country's laws but would they be comfortable seeing people post disgusting things about them? 
3. NEVER and Don't participate in FANWARS. We don't attack we defend. We respect all artists. If ever trolls come and spread hate, reply with with respect and love, that would make them shut up. Our boys are humble and respectful and they are our role models so be like them. Or just report their comments. Or just tell them to better go and stream their fave's m/v 
4. We stan talent. We stan 9 individuals in this group. 9 or None. Never 8, never 7, never 6, never 5, never 4, never 3, never 2, NEVER 1. We stan a family. 
5. STAY don't STRAY. 

Comment what I missed. I love STRAY KIDS and you, STAYS.
