author: @mjs1278
text:
Their mask at the end ended me. It's such a powerful message for me, even tho i don't get what is the link with the song. But to me, their masks represent how i am unable to talk about my problems to my close ones. I know that you can still talk with a mask like they have, but it kinda show how i mute myself, because i don't know who would listen and who i should talk to. 

I don't have any diagnosited (fuck i can't even spell it) problem, but i am pretty sure i had depression a few years ago and contemplated suicide a few times too, along with self-harm and food disorders. To me, the theme of the song only reminds me of the voices of others that i imagine and that are killing me from the inside, and this little voice always here to tell me i'm a failure. And..idk, the whole song + masks mean a lot to me and i don't even know why i wrote this haha.. 
Anyway, i just want Stray Kids to be happy and treated like human beings.

author: @blahblahblah855
text: Been a Fan of Stray Kids since D-1 and in the Stray Kids survival show. We were called the Nameless fandom back then and now we’re called stays💖 seeing them grow now makes me feel so emotional and their song just before their debut always touches my heart and now they have a new album im so proud that they got the chance to show their talents, composing their own songs, to show what they can do in front of others. I love how they write songs about our social issues, their own problems and worries, and even some old memories they had before their debut. I supported them ever since. I can totally see their hardwork before their debut. I’ll never forget how the group almost give up because Minho and Felix got eliminated and then there’s Chan who stand strong for the team because they are struggling because the two members got eliminated and i love how chan takes care of the whole group, he even works his ass out until morning without resting just for the group so that they’ll rise. I love how this group Didn’t come from JYP but Chan himself made this group. They always get criticised but they never let their guards down because they know they got Chan who’s always there whenever they needed him the most. I love their Teamwork, they’re helping each other so that no one would be in the bottom. I love how they can work their ass out just to teach their Brother who’s struggling in the practice. I just love everything about them being humble, helping each other out. I witnessed all of their struggles ever since they are Trainees. I love how they are patiently waiting for their debut. And seeing all of these things that turned out so well makes me so proud that from their struggles before and now here they are shining and will keep rising. I never saw this kind of rookies they are a monster rookies🤙🏻🤙🏻

author: @aaliyahu0904
text: A few months ago, before this comeback I was contemplating suicide. I was always a stay and always will be, and at the time my anxiety got too much for me to handle, and my mom took me for help. They said with the voices I hear and see I could be schizophrenic. Here I am, on my way to recovery...and even though I heard this song many times before, I never actually listened. I cried and I am crying as I type this out. So thank you Stray Kids, for being there for me and giving me songs to listen to that I can relate to. Thank you Stray Kids, because if it weren't for these lyrics that you have given me, I may not have been here today. ♥️

author: @lee3561
text:
not to be dramatic but they've honestly been the only thing that kept me going recently. i don't want to know where i would be now if it wasn't for this group of incredibly talented, goofy, lovable human beings. this song makes me cry because it reminds me of the times where i've been at my absolute lowest, and the voices were the only thing i had; they were the only ones there when i'd cry myself to sleep, when i'd think about the future, and when all i did was simply exist. 

but chan and woojin's voices were always there to remind me to not listen, to "step out of them." and now whenever i'm low, at the voices return, i hear chan and woojin telling me to stay strong. i've never met skz and probably never will, but they comfort me better than anyone else in this world can even hope to, and for that i will love them forever.

author: @yanaeliesa
text: So i have a story. In school i had 99% of the teachers and friends who would put me down every single day. Each day they would always have something to say especially the teachers. "I heard you were being rude u wont get anywhere no one will want you like this" "ur fat so its ok" "how can some people be so stupid as if u were never taught in school?" And many more of these irrelevant voices i keep hearing day and day for many years. I cried first alone then in my house then it got worse i cried in school open public she didnt bat a single eyelash i was thankful my friends were beside me but she really hurt me emotionally mentally physically. And for a fact she didnt even teach me anything. All the As i got were on my own effort no one else. Then my own relatives kept questioning me. I really was about to give up and one day my mind and my body couldnt take it no more so it shut down. I was out for 3 weeks. I woke up afterwards with no memory of anything but myself and my parents. I had nothing to relate to so i had to cope all alone. I made it this far.  Then i found this song. I found stray kids. I got emotional bc i truly understand. Finally. What i want to say is that if i can go through it so can you. We all can.

author: @possesed1113
text: I haven't any words and gestures for explanation of my emotions during watching this perfomance. I don't like to allocate the one song as the best in comparison with another song, especially in case of Stray Kids, i mean choosing the best song of Stray Kids and comparing them to each other. It doesn't work with their songs, because Stray Kids and their music are special, DIFFERENT, the best among rookies in the last 5 years in all respects IN MY OPINION. (I listen to k-pop since 2014) During the last 5 years a lot of very talented groups made their debut, but none of them I remembered as well as Stray Kids were remembered along with another my faves: BTS, FT Island, Shinee. This perfomance like their other perfomances has individual mood, atmosphere, palette of colors, technics, emphasises on a huge number of small details: great expressions of the boys, landscapes, so smooth and the same time sharp transitions between locations. STAY here and together! ✨ Diamonds of the 21st century!❤

author: @fabianealvescampos3976
text: Maybe you'll never see my comment, but I'll talk anyway. I suffered a lot because of these voices and could not follow my thoughts, and I thanked them with tears of joy as I saw the words of the song. You have changed my life in a way that I do not even understand. Thank you. Thank you very much. My eyes fill with tears and tears when I listen to Voices, I finally found the right words to be said and heard. You made me have a reason to wake up and try to be happy. Once more, thank you. Chan Oppa, Hyun Jin, Chang Bin, Woo Jin Oppa, Jeong In, Felix, Min Ho Oppa, Seung Min and Ji Sung, I love you guys, and I am very excited about being there and being part of my life. I'm not sure if it's going to be all right because I'm using an application to translate it better for you, but I hope you have felt my love for you. Stray Kids Fighting. Stay Fighting, we can do this.

author: @greywaren69
text: Stray kids put so much effort into every song and they all have such powerful messages that are so beautiful. Voices is just one example. It had such a strong meaning and beautiful lyrics. And they sing each song with such emotion it makes me cry listening to it. For example in this song (especially the bridge) they sound so tired of everything they have been through it makes me want to hug them and tell them it'll be ok and that I'm here for them. Like the bit in the bridge after Minho's part when Jisung and Changbin rap perfectly and you can just feel the emotion and the passion they are showing. And when  Chan says 'there's so many voices' he just sounds like he has given up. On a happier note, the visuals in the video are NO JOKE. Anyway Stray Kids 사랑해요 Take care of yourselves and keep healthy. Stray kids, Stay FIGHTING

author: @garretburrow
text:
Lemme tell you why these boys are rookie kings. In the ancient times of East Asia, when kings and queens would give birth to princes, the king would commission men of great renown to train and educate their son. Great philosophers and teachers would train their mind, & the greatest & most deadly martial artists would prepare their bodies for war; all in an effort to prepare them to one day inherit their father's kingdom(watch Marco Polo on Netflix to see what I mean.)
Nowadays, these princes don't go to war, but the comparison still applies. JYP is the king, & Stray Kids are his princes...or, to say it another way:
Rookie Kings.

author: @alyssabrelleayos6356
text: This video is not just aesthetically pleasing, visuals, talents or whatsoever you've seen but it also has a deep meaning. Changbin mentioned before that we'll love Voices since it has something that was similar to 'Hellevator' and it really is. Not just the MV that has similitarities but also the lyrics itself. People around them was against their dream and no one seemed to be in favor with them on whatever they do but inspite of that, they still do their best to persue their dreams no matter what. As you can see, they're wearing a mask. It's like it symbolizes that they're being suffocated by those people who keep on telling them to give up their dreams. As soon as they said "step out of them voices" they were being nagged by someone. Those people keep on repeating what they say to the point that their words are making them dizzy. In the end of the choreography, as you can see, their other hand was placed on their mouth and the other hand is at the back of their head and it's completely obvious that it's based on the lyrics "Break free from the voices in my head". It's like they can't say what they wanted to bcs there's a lot of people who keep on raising their voices towards them and it came to the point that they can't speak freely cuz they might judge them again. Im not really sure abt this HAHA imtiredtypingtho HAHAHA im not sure either if u get my point. i still have a lot to say but ermm. Sorry for my eng. Byeeee stream MY PACE.

Okay... so theres a concept behind this video~

first of all, the mask at the end of the video. At first i was like... why is their mask around their mouths? The song is about poeple talking behind you back and you being trapped and they should have worn earphones to show their blocking out the sound or voices, then i realized...

Thier wearing a MASK over their face, to mask themselves and not show their trueselves.. in other words, a facade.

And they take off their mask, to show the true identity and they listen to the voices but stand up for themselves~ 

And they realize who they and' i am who...'

author: @akiramin3870
text: When I was 7 my parents took me to a different country to live a better life since at the time we were extremely poor, but at least we were happy. The years passed by and I started feeling things that were hard for me to explain. By myself I had realized I had gotten depression and anxiety. I never told anyone because I never wanted to go to the doctor's. For me the doctors always left me so traumatized that I didn't even want to think about it. So I stayed quiet and just endured with the pain myself. I started feeling like a caged in bird and my mom never understood why I stay up in my room all day. I push myself away from everyone because I feel like the more I get to know them the more it will hurt me when they leave from the world. I'm now 24 years old and I've lived 17 years away from my relatives in my home country. At the beginning of this year we had decided we'd go back to our home country to start our own family business and to see our relatives again but...come July of this year my grandpa ends up passing away due to lung cancer. It was on its late stage and it ended up spreading everywhere in his body. I had come to realize that you can always find the time to explore. You can always make money. You can always make more friends no matter where you go. Money is not worth anything when it comes to love. There is so much time spent that you can never gain back. My mom always had me up to date with my grandpa so at least we got to see the funeral, but what hurts the most is that I've missed 17 years of him telling me wise and entertaining stories. I've missed so many ice creams we could have gotten together. I've missed all the family gatherings for the holidays and all the birthdays. Most importantly I've missed out on hugging him and kissing his cheek for 17 years. At school all the kids would always brag about going to their grandparents houses for the weekends for some special events. I always stayed quiet about those days. Just today my dad had called in to my job. He told my manager to let me go home earlier and to not tell me the reason why. They ended up closing anyways because a severe storm had formed. Once I arrived home my mom tells me that my other grandpa passed away. You could have had a really nice day but upon hearing news like this your world comes crashing in just mere seconds; however, the best part of my day is when I can run away from all the pain. When I can forget about everything and be reassured that everything will be alright. To me music is the best gateway out of hell and Stray Kids sure help out a lot. When I saw the recommendation to watch Hellevator I'm glad I clicked on the video. That was a year back or around there but when I had read the lyrics I was so impressed. I was moved and touched so I wondered who is this group? Why have I not heard of them yet? Why are they this good? They took all the frustration I'm feeling and managed to make it into a song! I didn't know about their show until Grrr came out since that's around the time I started watching it. Before I knew it I was already a fan. I listened to 3racha before I started watching the show since a friend had told me about them. The more information on them I kept receiving the more curious I kept getting. Each time I wanted to know more and more. To be honest at times I feel like I haven't even fully grasped all of it because the first thing I asked myself when I heard this song is, "They made this song??! They...Stray Kids.....3racha....Bang Chan a 22 year old Seo Changbin a 20 year old and Han Jisung a 19 year old(he has about a month but whatever)made a song like this?! I don't get it.....how is this possible???" These questions are what I ask myself because I keep feeling as if they've read my mind. I feel like we're so close when we're separated by oceans and land. I have my parents right by my side. I have Stray Kids in my heart telling me to escape from the voices in my head or I will go mad. This in itself is the best therapy I could ever ask for. So why would I need to go to the doctor's and waste more money when all they will do is prescribe drugs to me that I will not be able to take in the first place? Or recommend me to speak with a stranger as if the stranger is the one I need help with when I just need the love and support of those whom I love? Love is so powerful it can break everything and that's what I've always believed in. So I'll hold on to that hope till the very last chance I get. I will stay with Stray Kids for as long as I'm alive I will not leave their music out of my heart. Please continue to be yourselves no matter what changes may come and I promise I will stay just as I am. Once a Stay always a Stay and I will always be proud to say that. Sorry for my extremely long message but I hope some of you will pass through this comment and just appreciate what you have in life. I love you all no matter what you look like or what happens in your life. I hope you can all achieve your goals and wishes and if not all at least one. Be proud to be yourself and always love yourself. Always remember someone out there loves you and if you don't think so then you just haven't met them yet; you're also lying to yourself. Stay strong fam. 💞💕

author: @TheHottestinspirit
text:
This song really deserved it's own mv but I am already happy with this performance video. Voices is THE song for me, just like how Grow Up did it to me and Voices did the same thing to me. Such a deep, meaningful song that everyone can relate. Sometime we just wanted people to shut up, all those useless insults or comparison or mocking words to stop, and let us do whatever we want but because of those voices sometime it's get to us and we wanted it to stop what even scarier is those voices now became our own voice that kept putting down ourselves, kept thinking we're the worst, kept making our own selves weak, we hated it yet we did the same to ourself, not loving our own self having such a low confidence in our own self. We need to stop it.

 Let's break free from these voices! Thank you Stray Kids, even though all of you are younger than me but I actually learn more from these kids, they're the future of KPOP, I am sure this group will be bigger in the future, it's okay take all your time to be on top! "Don't compare yourself with others it's okay to run slower"

author: @lexiwilliams382
text:
This is my new favorite song!!! I appreciate Stray Kids so so much! I've been a Stay since pre-debut!!! They are extremely inspirational and motivated to let people hear what they have to say. They aren't afraid of the truth but rather face it and spread the word. I am overwhelmed with pride and love for these boys. I can't wait to continue watching them progress in their fame. They deserve the world. If you don't stan yet... You better stan them now.
.
.
On another note I'm so so proud and happy that Jeongin and Minho are finally getting the lines they deserve. Their voices are so beautiful. It's official that Changbin is the world's best rapper. If you don't agree, it's okay. Hyunjin has improved in so so many areas and I really could not be prouder. Jisung is so talented and beautiful... I literally have no words for him. He's absolutely amazing and impresses me more with everything he does. Seungmin and Woojin are still killing the notes and I'm so happy for them. Their voices are gorgeous and this album suits their voices very very well. Felix and his deep voice man... It still gets me... I mean, how in the world would we live had he not debuted with Stray Kids? He's so talented and beautiful and..... CHANGLIX. Y'all better not be sleeping on this ship.... Anyways... I'm so so so proud of Chan. He's such a great leader and I think the other members really do look up to him and he is doing so well. He can sing and rap, like boy, I want him to have some raps in the Stray Kids songs every once in a while. He deserves to be a rapper. His voice is still beautiful though!!! Overall though, I really appreciate his humor. It really keeps us all happy and positive. Welp that's it for this novel, until next time Stays.

author: @acwhos
text:
I really don't understand how people hate on Stray Kids. I'm not a hardcore stan or anything, but I keep up with their music and totally support them, the members, their values, and admire their passion and talent. They're such a recently debuted group, having so many haters already? I just don't understand. They're truly amazing.

Haters aside, this is the first time I've heard this song since comeback. I haven't had time to listen to the full album yet, but so far it's been a total hit with me. It's as if they've been performing and writing for at least over a year already (not including predebut time).

author: @fivefive9362
text:
Korea and people in general should stop sleeping on stray kids. People would often look down on groups like stray kids and say their only gaining the popularity they have because they’re from a big company. Saying stuff like groups from a small company have to work much harder to be acknowledge whereas groups like stray kids gain immediate popularity. 

However, people doesn’t realize that inside these big companies it is way more competitive. In order for stray kids to debut they have to constantly compete with other trainees. For example, cuz jyp is so big and competitive so many people would come and go because not everyone can debut. Bang chan withstand all of that for 7 years before he can finally debut as a jyp group. Stray kids work hard to get where they are. They deserve all and more success. 

Please don’t be prejudiced against them or their popularity just because they’re from a big company. Have an open heart and listen to their music before deciding to blindly dislike them. 

❤️❤️❤️ Btw ‘voices’ is such an awesome song!!! I got chills

author: @mimitran7216
text:
They are behind masks because they have to hide their true voices and thoughts away from the toxic world full of judgement and hate but as time past, they slowly take off the masks, symbolizing that It is a time to speak out. They can’t hide behind a mask no more. THEY have to be the voice who doesn’t have one. Despite the hate in the world, the world needs to know how they feel and what they’re going through. This is truly such a beautiful song and mv.

Stray kids talks about falling down in life, teenage rebellion, losing yourself, being envious, school life and etc. They really are trying to shine a light to the public about what people are going through. They are giving a voice to people who does not have one.

I have much respect for them and I hope fans will continue to support them because they are certainly giving us support through their songs. They give life advice to make us into a better us. Hope they will become very successful one day.

author: @moli2419
text:
I Stan them since predebut, I saw them when they were 9,I saw them when they were 8,I saw them when they were 7 and I also saw them when we finally know they were going to debut with 9 kids,Kim WooJin,Bang Chan,Lee MinHo,Seo ChangBin,Hwang HyunJin,Han JiSung,Lee Felix,Kim SeungMin and Yang Jeong In;I was happy when they released a Mixtape and I watched all their MV's, I waited until they finally release "I Am Not",their album debut, I've been night without sleep watching to their music videos,climbing visits to District 9 and Mirror. I waited for them again, hearing to the same 14 song(+3Racha songs) every single day and night until now, that they released their second mini album "I Am Who". It's been a long time a know them,almost a year,and now I think I can say that I saw them grown up, not only in age but also like a group,they became better and better since I met them. Now, I am very proud of them,and very proud of see my 9 boys growing together,having fun together, smiling and crying together and I can't even be more proud of being a STAY,of being part of this huge family,which is growing and growing more with each passing day and I am happy to say that while I am conscious, I will never leave them, I will be at their side at every moment and I will see them reach the top and dreams. With no hesitate I'm gonna say it, I love you boys.

Stays always with Stray Kids.

author: @ajgiza9866
text: I love this song because the kind of intensity is suspenseful and the song is really well composed. You could also slow this song down into a ballad. I would really love to see Seungmin and Hyunjin do a individual cover but more acoustic, I would love to see the vocals and rapping stripped down. I heard from a very wise PD once “A debut has to be great but the 1st and 2nd comeback have to be even better”. I definitely think Stray Kids’ comeback accomplished that. All the music was 100 times better, (and I already loved their debut album with District 9 and 3rd eye and all the other amazing songs). The Stay fandom became twice as big from this comeback so i would love to see Stray Kids’ music in their next comeback and eventually their music evolution over time. I know Stray Kids will make it big, so I’m rooting for them. Stray Kids Fighting!

author: @aiurihoon996
text: I actually didn't know each one of them before back when JYP boy group trainees were popping from here and there because seriously it was really hard to find informations about it but I was happy because finally a new group may come out any time soon then suddenly JYP releases Hellevator and I thought it was their debut and found out later it was for their survival program. I have been a fan since the first time I saw hellevator 30 minutes after it was released. Being with them since those pre-debut days really makes me emotional seeing the hardships they had to encounter to reach this goal of theirs to reach their dreams. The criticism they received during the survival show and almost not being able to debut. It's just so overwhelming seeing them where they are now out here not just giving us great songs but meaningful at the same time and things we all could relate too. They are out here showing us their stories and comforting each one of us with every problem we all have. STRAY KIDS IF YOU ARE READING THIS THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR BRINGING BRIGHTNESS BACK INTO MY LIFE! Your songs are what keeps me going and I hope you get to reach more people out there through your songs and we STAYs will always be here for all of you no matter what. Depend on us like how we depend on you guys! We can be your light bearer just as you guys are ours. Stay healthy always and let's keep moving on our own pace together and shut the voices that brings us all down! 💕💕💕 Stray Kids Fighting! 💕💕💕

author: @mmaantj
text:
This song really cheered me up. I just learned that my homeroom teacher (dutch: mentor, idk if i used the right word) is the one I had during the time in my life where I kind of had suicidal thoughts and I’m pretty sure I wasn’t really happy. 

So these last 2 years of high school are gonna be hell, was my first reaction. But then; I’ve changed, my teacher’s changed. 13 year old me would have cried and cried for days. I only cried for 10 minutes and after this video realized that my hatred for her might just be a result of the state I was in when I met her. So basically they’re just voices telling me to hate her. That’s how this song helped me just now. So if I stay optimistic, I might survive this.

So, for the 5th time in my life, I’m gonna pack my books and hope for the best.

author: @tarakana8805
text: *Being a predebut fan, this is really hard to watch all the way without crying. Hellevator was the first the world had seen of them. That was only October 6th of last year. They've come such a long way in less than a year. Each and every one of them have gone through something in their life that everyone can relate to in some way, which they talk about in a lot of their music. Even at such a young age, they're accomplishing so much. They're talking about topics that nobody has before. They aren't your normal rookie group, either. They've been so close ever since their trainee days, which you don't normally see. Thank you, Stray Kids, for being such an inspiration to me and other STAYs. I believe you all will continue to accomplish many things in the future. We will STAY by your side, all the way. But take all the time you need. It's okay to go slow. Until then, don't compare yourselves.*

author: @TheHottestinspirit
text: *At first I was this is sure a fanmade because it's too good to be true, and then I was screaming. This song really deserved it's own mv but I am already happy with this performance video. Voices is THE song for me, just like how Grow Up did it to me and Voices did the same thing to me. Such a deep, meaningful song that everyone can relate. Sometime we just wanted people to shut up, all those useless insults or comparison or mocking words to stop, and let us do whatever we want but because of those voices sometime it's get to us and we wanted it to stop even scarier is those voices are actually our own voice that kept putting down ourselves, kept thinking we're the worst, kept making our ownselves weak, we hated it yet we did the same to ourself, not loving our ownself having such a low confidence in our ownself. We need to stop it. Thank you Stray Kids, even though all of you are younger than me but I actually learn more from these kids, they're the future of KPOP, I am sure this group will be bigger in the future, it's okay take all your time to be on top! "Don't compare yourself with others it's okay to run slower"*

author: @loxee4769
text:
This song makes me cry. I've been dealing with mental issues my whole life long, but only a few years ago have I developed an eating disorder, which fills my head with voices like no disease has ever done before. This song radiates a feeling I know all too well. This song portrays my feelings of being suffocated and anxious perfectly, it makes me feel understood.
Thank you guys so much for this song. There's so much happening in my life right now and I am genuinely thankful for a song so comforting and helpful to your fans. Thank you so much.
